{"lemma":"عَقِيقِ","slug":"عَقِيقِ","root":"ع.ق.ق","root_slug":"ع-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29816"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ravine, canyon, kloof"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"agate","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"carnelian","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic עקיק, unless both are from a third source."},"ipa":["/ʕa.qiːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29816","headword_ar":"عَقِيقٌ","root":"Eq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cleft, split, slit, ripped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoquwqN","text_ar":"مَعْقُوقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any channel which the water of a torrent has cloven"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, * K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of old"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made wide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a valley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEiq~apN","text_ar":"اَعِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"عَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"عَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pools of water in cleft furrows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) and some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red sands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqiyqapN","text_ar":"عَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Carnelian;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuwS","text_ar":"فُصُوص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones that are set in rings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraz","text_ar":"خَرَز"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"precious stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSuwS","text_ar":"فُصُوص"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are made;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existing in ElYemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near to Esh-Shihr, said by Et-Teefáshee to be brought from mines thereof at San'à,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and on the shores of the Sea of Roomeeyeh; one kind thereof is of a turbid appearance, like water running from salted flesh-meat, and having in it faint white lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"Et-Teefáshee says,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is what is known by the appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrTbY","text_ar":"الرطبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in my original];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best kind is the red; then, the yellow; then, the white; and the other kinds are bad: or, as some"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2097},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"say, the streaked"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$aT~ab","text_ar":"المُشَطَّب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the best:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [I omit some absurd assertions in the K and TA respecting various virtues supposed to be possessed by this stone:] the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"عَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaqiyqu AlyamaAniY~u","text_ar":"العَقِيقُ اليَمَانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appel-lation applied by some to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The agate."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","O","K","TA","AHn"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}